itemLabel: Alexander Murray, 1st Baron Murray of Elibank

wikipedia_page.main: Alexander William Charles Oliphant Murray, 1st Baron Murray of Elibank  (12 April 1870 – 13 September 1920), called The Master of Elibank between 1871 and 1912, was a Scottish nobleman and  Liberal politician. He served as Parliamentary Secretary to the Treasury (Chief Government Whip) under H. H. Asquith between 1910 and 1912, when he was forced to resign after being implicated in the Marconi scandal.
